Task:

1.	Run any 5 commands in single shell script
 ls -lrt
 du
 df
 free -m
 one file
 one directory

2. use the read command twice and one is to create a file and another one is to create a directory
and file and directory should have read write permission

----------------------------------------------------------------------------


what is Shell script:

1. To automate the tasks/small chunk of code 
2. we can run many task /many command in a single file using shell script 

Scenario 1:

If I want to create 100 files with some permission or different name - using shell script we can achieve

Scenario 2:

VM - have memory issue , it consume more memory ( if it is exceed 80% - it should alert us )

scenario 3:
Backup of log file 

everyday logs will generate - it will occupy more memory , to avoid this one , everyday night at sometime 
need to copy the log file and tar that log file and original log file should be deleted.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Two types of shells

1. Bourne shell ( terminal start with $ ) /bin/bash
2. C shell ( terminal start with %)

Definition:

A shell script is an command line interpreter and is used to perform manipulation , execution , deletion and 
displaying result.

realtime scenario:

1. Database backup and deletion
2. Memory usage alert
3. Backup the log files
4. cron job - scheduled jobs for cleanup activites


----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic shell script structure

#!/bin/bash -> Hashbang/shebang line -> what it represent ? This is the 1st line of the shell script , which
is used to represent that file is going to use bourne shell to execute the script.

Comments:
1.	#author : ABC 
2.	#Date : 28.10.2025
3.	#Desc - shell script description

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/bash
#Author : ABC
#Date   : 28/10/2025
#Desc   : Adding two numbers

<script>


-------------------------------------------
How to create the shell script:

1.	Create a file
2.	save the file with extension.sh
   example: <filename>.sh

vi <filename.sh> 

<script>

----------------------------------------------------
How to execute the shell script

syntax 1

sh <filename.sh>

example:

sh samplefile.sh

-----------------------------------
syntax 2 :

./<filename.sh>

example:

./<samplefile.sh>

------------------------------------------------------
#!/bin/bash
#Author: ABC
#Date: 28/10/25
#Descrption: Example shell script

touch sampletextfile

Output:
@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ sh demo.sh
6
@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ ls -lrth
total 12K
