-rw-rw-rw-  1 codespace codespace  115 Oct 28 15:04 demo.sh
-rw-rw-rw-  1 codespace codespace    0 Oct 28 15:06 sampletextfile


--------------------------------------------------------------
Read : Read command s going to read the value from the CLI (end user need to provide) / terminal
whenever we are going to execute the shell script

echo: It provide the Value/output 


For example:

Read the file name and create the file based on the filename and give all the permission to the file

#!/bin/bash
#Author : ABC
#Date : 28.10.25
#Description : Read the file name and create the file based on the filename and give all the permission to the file

echo "enter the file name" 
read filename

echo "the filename is $filename"

touch $filename
chmod 777 $filename

output:

@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ sh shell.sh
enter the file name - file01.txt
file01.txt
shell.sh: 14: Syntax error: Unterminated quoted string
@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ vi shell.sh
@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ vi shell.sh
@visuweshkris ➜ /workspaces/shell-script (main) $ sh shell.sh
enter the file name
demotxtfile
the filename is demotxtfile
